#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn35.89"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.89:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.89:0.2"
msgid "9. Channavagga "
msgstr "9. With Channa "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn35.89:0.3"
msgid "89. Bāhiyasutta "
msgstr "89. With Bāhiya "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn35.89:1.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā bāhiyo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā bāhiyo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Venerable Bāhiya went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.89:1.2"
msgid "“sādhu me, bhante, bhagavā saṅkhittena dhammaṃ desetu, yamahaṃ bhagavato dhammaṃ sutvā eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī pahitatto vihareyyan”ti. "
msgstr "“Sir, may the Buddha please teach me Dhamma in brief. When I’ve heard it, I’ll live alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn35.89:2.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, bāhiya, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Bāhiya? "

msgctxt "sn35.89:2.2"
msgid "cakkhu niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "Is the eye permanent or impermanent?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn35.89:3.1"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn35.89:4.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn35.89:5.1"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn35.89:6.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ: "
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and liable to fall apart, is it fit to be regarded thus: "

msgctxt "sn35.89:6.2"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti? "
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.64, sc7
msgctxt "sn35.89:7.1"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "sn35.89:8.1"
msgid "“Rūpā niccā vā aniccā vā”ti? "
msgstr "“Are sights … "

#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "sn35.89:9.1"
msgid "“Aniccā, bhante” … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.89:9.2"
msgid "cakkhuviññāṇaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "eye consciousness … "

msgctxt "sn35.89:9.3"
msgid "cakkhusamphasso … pe … "
msgstr "eye contact … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.89:9.4"
msgid "yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "The pleasant, painful, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by mind contact: is that permanent or impermanent?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "sn35.89:10.1"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "sn35.89:11.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "sn35.89:12.1"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "sn35.89:13.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ: "
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and liable to fall apart, is it fit to be regarded thus: "

msgctxt "sn35.89:13.2"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti? "
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "sn35.89:14.1"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc15
msgctxt "sn35.89:15.1"
msgid "“Evaṃ passaṃ, bāhiya, sutavā ariyasāvako cakkhusmimpi nibbindati, rūpesupi nibbindati, cakkhuviññāṇepi nibbindati, cakkhusamphassepi nibbindati … pe … "
msgstr "“Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with the eye, sights, eye consciousness, and eye contact. And they grow disillusioned with the painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by eye contact. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.89:15.2"
msgid "yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tasmimpi nibbindati. "
msgstr "They grow disillusioned with the ear … nose … tongue … body … mind … painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by mind contact. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.89:15.3"
msgid "Nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati; vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti. "
msgstr "Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re freed. When they’re freed, they know they’re freed. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.89:15.4"
msgid "‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānātī”ti. "
msgstr "They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "sn35.89:16.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā bāhiyo bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi. "
msgstr "And then Venerable Bāhiya approved and agreed with what the Buddha said. He got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right, before leaving. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.89:16.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā bāhiyo eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsi. "
msgstr "Then Bāhiya, living alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute, soon realized the supreme end of the spiritual path in this very life. He lived having achieved with his own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.89:16.3"
msgid "“Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā”ti abbhaññāsi. "
msgstr "He understood: “Rebirth is ended; the spiritual journey has been completed; what had to be done has been done; there is no return to any state of existence.” "

msgctxt "sn35.89:16.4"
msgid "Aññataro ca panāyasmā bāhiyo arahataṃ ahosīti. "
msgstr "And Venerable Bāhiya became one of the perfected. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.89:16.5"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ. "
msgstr ""

